vel:** High  \n**Implications:** Inadequate safeguards increase breach risks and operational disruptions.  \n\n**Prioritized Actions:**  \n1. **Implement real-time monitoring** with anomaly detection.  \n   - *Informatica Solution:* Partnership with **securiti.ai** for API threat protection.  \n2. **Deploy backup/recovery plans** with geo-redundancy.  \n   - *Informatica Solution:* **Cloud Data Ingestion and Replication (CDIR)**.  \n3. **Enforce log retention** (1+ year) for audits.  \n\n---\n\n### 4. **Data Breach Notification (50% Compliance)**  \n**Risk Level:** Moderate  \n**Implications:** Delayed notifications may escalate regulatory scrutiny.  \n\n**Prioritized Actions:**  \n1. **Enhance breach alerts** to notify affected users immediately.  \n\n---\n\n### 5. **Data Retention & Erasure (50% Compliance)**  \n**Risk Level:** Moderate  \n**Implications:** Retaining data beyond necessity violates DPDP Section 8(1).  \n\n**Prioritized Actions:**  \n1. **Adopt secure erasure protocols** (e.g., NIST 800-88).  \n   - *Informatica Solution:* Compliant data erasure tools.  \n\n---\n\n### 6. **Third-Party Processing (0% Compliance)**  \n**Risk Level:** Critical  \n**Implications:** Unregulated third-party access risks data misuse.  \n\n**Prioritized Actions:**  \n1. **Establish binding contracts** with processors (DPDP Section 6(f)).  \n2. **Mandate security safeguards** in agreements.  \n\n---\n\n### 7. **Cross-Border Data Transfers (50% Compliance)**  \n**Risk Level:** High  \n**Implications:** Non-adherence to localization norms may trigger sanctions.  \n\n**Prioritized Actions:**  \n1. **Review storage practices** for RBI/IRDAI compliance.  \n   - *Informatica Solution:* **Data Engineering Integration** for lineage tracking.  \n2. **Develop a transfer framework** per DPDP Section 14.  \n\n---\n\n## Strategic Recommendations  \n1. **Leverage Informatica Solutions** to automate:  \n   - Consent management (**CDGC/CDAM**).  \n   - Data localization tracking (**Data Eng