(1)(e)).  \n\n### 4. Data Breach Notification (33.3%)  \n**Risk Level: High**  \n* **Implications:** Regulatory action for missed 72-hour reporting deadlines.  \n* **Actions:**  \n  1. Develop an incident response playbook with escalation paths.  \n  2. Conduct breach simulation drills to test notification workflows.  \n\n### 5. Data Retention & Erasure (62.5%)  \n**Risk Level: Medium**  \n* **Implications:** Over-retention risks violating storage limitation principles.  \n* **Actions:**  \n  1. Automate erasure triggers based on retention policies.  \n  2. Integrate data lifecycle management tools to purge obsolete records.  \n\n### 6. Cross-Border Data Transfers (33.3%)  \n**Risk Level: Critical**  \n* **Implications:** Violations of RBI/IRDAI localization mandates.  \n* **Actions:**  \n  1. Enforce geo-fencing to block unauthorized transfers.  \n  2. Map all data flows to identify non-compliant transfers.  \n\n---\n\n## Prioritized Action Plan  \n1. **Immediate (0ďż˝30 days):**  \n   * Draft updated privacy notices (Data Collection).  \n   * Initiate breach response protocol development (Security).  \n\n2. **Short-Term (30ďż˝90 days):**  \n   * Deploy automated rights request tracking (Data Principal Rights).  \n   * Pilot geo-redundant backups (Security).  \n\n3. **Long-Term (90ďż˝180 days):**  \n   * Conduct organization-wide DPDP training (Documentation).  \n   * Appoint a Data Protection Officer (Compliance).  \n\n---\n\n## Strategic Recommendations  \n* **Leverage technology** to automate compliance workflows (e.g., data classification, erasure).  \n* **Adopt a risk-based approach**, focusing first on high-impact gaps (Security, Cross-Border Transfers).  \n* **Partner with Informatica experts** to close gaps efficiently.  \n\n**Contact:** info@datainfa.com for DPDP implementation support.  \n```",
