dedicated web portals or email.  \n2. Publish transparent response timelines (e.g., 30 days for access requests) on all customer-facing platforms.  \n\n---\n\n### 3. Data Security Measures (40%)  \n**Risk Level:** **Medium**  \n**Implications:** Inadequate log retention and storage mechanisms hinder breach investigations and audit readiness.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. Implement mandatory 1-year log retention policies using **Informatica Data Privacy Management (DPM)** for secure storage.  \n\n---\n\n### 4. Data Breach Notification (16.7%)  \n**Risk Level:** **High**  \n**Implications:** Delayed breach reporting beyond 72 hours (DPDP Section 7(1)) may trigger fines.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. Automate breach detection and notification workflows with **Informatica Cloud Application Integration (CAI)**.  \n\n---\n\n### 5. Data Retention and Erasure (25%)  \n**Risk Level:** **Medium**  \n**Implications:** Manual processes delay compliance with DPDP Section 8 erasure requirements.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. Automate policy-driven erasure via **Informatica Cloud Data Integration (CDI)**.  \n2. Trigger 48-hour deletion notices using **CAI**.  \n\n---\n\n### 6. Cross-Border Data Transfers (16.7%)  \n**Risk Level:** **Critical**  \n**Implications:** Unrestricted data transfers outside India violate DPDP Section 12(4).  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. Enforce location-based access controls with **Informatica Cloud Data Access Management (CDAM)**.  \n\n---\n\n## Strategic Recommendations  \n1. **Prioritize High-Risk Areas:** Focus on consent management, breach notification, and cross-border transfers using **Informatica CDGC** and **DPM**.  \n2. **Automate Compliance Workflows:** Leverage **Informatica CAI** and **CDI** to reduce manual errors in erasure and breach response.  \n3. **Conduct Quarterly Audits:** Use **Informatica CLAIRE GPT** to monitor unauthorized data activities.  \n\n---\n\n**Partner with Informatica Experts** to close compliance gaps efficiently.  \n**Con