itized Actions:**  \n1. Deploy **Informatica Dynamic Data Masking** and **Persistent Data Masking** for end-to-end data protection.  \n2. Strengthen access controls with **Informatica Cloud Data Access Management (CDAM)** for authentication and logging.  \n3. Implement **Informaticaďż˝s Log Analyzer** to monitor unauthorized access in real-time.  \n\n---\n\n### 4. Data Breach Notification (66.7% Compliance)  \n**Risk Level:** Medium  \n**Implications:** Missed 72-hour reporting windows could trigger penalties.  \n\n**Recommendation:**  \n* Automate breach detection and reporting workflows using **Informatica Cloud Application Integration (CAI)**.  \n\n---\n\n### 5. Data Retention & Erasure (50% Compliance)  \n**Risk Level:** Medium  \n**Implications:** Non-compliance with erasure requests undermines user trust.  \n\n**Actions:**  \n1. Automate data deletion workflows with **Informatica Master Data Management (CMDM)**.  \n2. Use **Informatica CAI** to trigger 48-hour deletion notices to users.  \n\n---\n\n### 6. Cross-Border Data Transfers (16.7% Compliance)  \n**Risk Level:** High  \n**Implications:** Violations of RBI/IRDAI localization mandates.  \n\n**Critical Steps:**  \n1. Track data flows with **Informatica Data Engineering Integration** to ensure domestic storage compliance.  \n2. Restrict transfers of sensitive data using **Informatica Cloud Data Governance Catalog**.  \n\n---\n\n### 7. Grievance Redressal (0% Compliance)  \n**Risk Level:** Critical  \n**Implications:** Lack of redressal mechanisms violates DPDP accountability requirements.  \n\n**Immediate Actions:**  \n1. Develop formal policies aligned with DPDP Section 10.  \n2. Integrate **Informatica CLAIRE GPT** for automated complaint tracking.  \n\n---\n\n## Strategic Recommendations  \n1. **Automate Compliance:** Deploy **Informaticaďż˝s end-to-end suite** (Data Privacy Management, CDAM, CDGC) to close gaps in security, governance, and monitoring.  \n2. **Documentation Framework:** Use **Informatica Enterprise Data Catalog** to automate records of processing activities.  \n3. **Training:** Conduct staff workshops on DPDP exemptions and breach protocols.  \n\n**Partner with Informatica experts to close gaps efficiently.**  \nContact **info@datainfa.com** for further understanding and DPDP implementation.  \n```",
