ws with **Informatica’s partnership solutions (e.g., securiti.ai)**.  \n\n---\n\n### 4. Data Breach Notification (83.3%)  \n**Risk Level:** Low  \n**Actions:**  \n* Enhance procedures to notify affected principals immediately.  \n\n---\n\n### 5. Data Retention and Erasure (37.5%)  \n**Risk Level:** High  \n**Implications:** Non-compliant storage, legal challenges.  \n**Actions:**  \n* Automate erasure processes with **Informatica’s data management solutions**.  \n* Optimize deletion mechanisms for expired data.  \n\n---\n\n### 6. Data Accuracy and Completeness (25.0%)  \n**Risk Level:** Moderate  \n**Actions:**  \n* Align policies with regulations using **Informatica Cloud Data Quality**.  \n* Enhance audit logging with **Informatica IICS** and **Log Analyzer**.  \n\n---\n\n### 7. Children's Data Protection (33.3%)  \n**Risk Level:** High  \n**Actions:**  \n* Develop technical frameworks for parental consent and age verification.  \n\n---\n\n### 8. Third-Party Processing (0.0%)  \n**Risk Level:** Critical  \n**Actions:**  \n* Mandate DPDP-aligned contracts with third parties.  \n* Include security safeguards in agreements.  \n\n---\n\n### 9. Cross-Border Data Transfers (0.0%)  \n**Risk Level:** Critical  \n**Actions:**  \n* Implement localization measures via **Informatica Cloud Data Integration**.  \n\n---\n\n### 10. Documentation & Compliance (30.0%)  \n**Risk Level:** Moderate  \n**Actions:**  \n* Schedule policy reviews and staff training on DPDP obligations.  \n\n---\n\n## Prioritized Action Plan  \n1. **Immediate (0–3 months):**  \n   * Deploy **Informatica Data Privacy Management** for principal rights and security.  \n   * Establish third-party contracts and data localization measures.  \n\n2. **Short-Term (3–6 months):**  \n   * Automate data erasure and accuracy checks.  \n   * Roll out RBAC/MFA with **Informatica CDAM**.  \n\n3. **Long-Term (6–12 months):**  \n   * Expand monitoring and breach response capabilities.  \n   * Implement child data safeguards