vel:** Critical  \n**Implications:** Exposure to breaches due to insufficient encryption and backup protocols.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. Apply **Informatica Dynamic Data Masking** to protect sensitive data in all environments.  \n2. Implement **geographically distributed backups** using **Informatica Cloud Data Ingestion and Replication (CDIR)**.  \n\n---\n\n### 4. Data Breach Notification (0.0%)  \n**Risk Level:** Critical  \n**Implications:** Regulatory penalties for missing **72-hour reporting** under **DPDP Section 7(2)(b)**.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. Develop an **incident escalation workflow** with automated alerts.  \n2. Integrate **Informatica Cloud Application Integration (CAI)** to trigger notifications.  \n\n---\n\n### 5. Data Retention and Erasure (0.0%)  \n**Risk Level:** High  \n**Implications:** Non-compliance with **DPDP Section 8** on secure deletion.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. Automate retention policies using **Informatica Cloud Data Integration (CDI)**.  \n2. Enforce **NIST 800-88-compliant erasure** via Informatica tools.  \n\n---\n\n### 6. Cross-Border Data Transfers (50.0%)  \n**Risk Level:** Moderate  \n**Implications:** Violations of **RBI/IRDAI localization norms**.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. Use **Informatica Cloud Data Integration** with region-specific processing to maintain residency.  \n\n---\n\n## Strategic Recommendations  \n1. **Prioritize High-Risk Areas:** Focus on breach notification, encryption, and erasure controls.  \n2. **Leverage Automation:** Deploy **Informatica Cloud Data Governance** for end-to-end policy enforcement.  \n3. **Upskilling:** Train teams on DPDP requirements and tool usage (e.g., **CLAIR GPT** for monitoring).  \n\n---\n\n**Partner with Informatica experts to close gaps efficiently.**  \nContact **info@datainfa.com** for DPDP implementation support.  \n```",
