res with **Informatica Data Access Management (CDAM)**.  \n2. Conduct regular audits using **Informatica Cloud Data Governance (CDGC)**.  \n\n---\n\n### 4. Data Breach Notification (50%)  \n**Risk Level:** High  \n**Implications:** Delayed or incomplete notifications violate DPDP Section 7.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. Enhance procedures to notify affected parties immediately.  \n2. Update templates to include all DPDP-mandated details.  \n\n---\n\n### 5. Data Retention & Erasure (62.5%)  \n**Risk Level:** Moderate  \n**Implications:** Non-compliance with deletion notices may trigger disputes.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. Automate 48-hour advance notices via **Informatica CAI**.  \n\n---\n\n### 6. Data Accuracy and Completeness (0%)  \n**Risk Level:** Critical  \n**Implications:** Inaccurate data undermines trust and compliance.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. Deploy **Informatica Cloud Data Quality (CDQ)** for profiling and cleansing.  \n2. Replace manual logs with automated tracking using **Informatica IICS** and **Log Analyzer**.  \n\n---\n\n### 7. Children’s Data Protection (50%)  \n**Risk Level:** High  \n**Implications:** Weak consent mechanisms risk violating DPDP Section 10.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. Integrate biometric or document-based parental verification.  \n2. Conduct a legal review of exemptions under DPDP Section 11.  \n\n---\n\n### 8. Third-Party Processing (50%)  \n**Risk Level:** Moderate  \n**Implications:** Unregulated third parties pose data misuse risks.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. Enforce contracts aligned with DPDP Section 6(f).  \n\n---\n\n### 9. Cross-Border Data Transfers (33.3%)  \n**Risk Level:** High  \n**Implications:** Unauthorized transfers violate localization norms.  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. Monitor data flows with **Informatica Data Engineering Integration**.  \n2. Block unauthorized transfers using **Informatica CDAM**.  \n\n---\n\n### 10. Grievance Redressal (16.7%)  \n**Risk Level:** Critical  \n**Implications:** Poor complaint handling breaches DPDP Section 13(3).  \n\n**Action Items:**  \n1. Form dedicated complaint teams with clear timelines.  \n2. Automate oversight using **Informatica CAI**.  \n\n---\n\n## Strategic Recommendations  \n1. **Prioritize Critical Gaps:** Focus on Data Accuracy, Principal Rights, and Breach Notification.  \n2. **Leverage Automation:** Deploy **Informatica CDGC, CDQ, and DPM** to streamline compliance.  \n3. **Training & Awareness:** Conduct staff workshops on DPDP exemptions and obligations.  \n\n---\n\n**Partner with Informatica experts to close gaps efficiently.**  \nContact **info@datainfa.com** for further understanding and DPDP implementation.  \n```",
